
[1]thesis

   THE'SIS, n. [L. thesis; Gr. a position, to set.]

   1. A position or proposition which a person advances and offers to
   maintain, or which is actually maintained by argument; a theme; a
   subject.

   2. In logic, every proposition may be divided into thesis and
   hypothesis. Thesis contains the thing affirmed or denied, and
   hypothesis the conditions of the affirmation or negation.
